{"lemma":"شُلُّ","slug":"شُلُّ","root":"ش.ل.ل","root_slug":"ش-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22913"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to drive, to goad, to prod, to propel (livestock)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lame, to paralyze"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"lame"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rope","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a linear measure of sixty cubits (ذِرَاع (ḏirāʕ))","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ش ل ل (š l l).\n\nFrom Aramaic אַשְׁלָא (ašlā, “rope”) (Classical Syriac ܐܻܝܫܠܴܐ (ʾīšlā, “rope”)), in Imperial Aramaic 𐡀𐡔𐡋 (ʾšl, “a surface measure”), from Akkadian 𒌑𒌃 (^ÚNINNI₅ /⁠ašlu⁠/, “rush; tow-rope; measuring rope; a linear measure of about 60 meters; a surface measure”). Doublet of أَسَل (ʔasal, “long and slender twigs; rush; spear”)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.ʃal.la/","/ʔa.ʃall/","/ʔaʃl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22913","headword_ar":"اَشَلُّ","root":"$l","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm, has become unsound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vitiated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deprived of the power of motion by an unsound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vitiated, state of its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euruwq","text_ar":"عُرُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veins"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nerves"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dried up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stiff:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm, has gone"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wasted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$al~aA='u","text_ar":"شَلَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadN $al~aA='u","text_ar":"يَدٌ شَلَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA) A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an arm, that will not comply with that which its possessor desires of it, by reason of disease therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN $al~aA='u","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ شَلَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An eye of which the sight has gone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Msb, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","Msb","K","Mgh"]}]}}